36template <typename Type,
37 bool sorted=false>
38struct hb_vector_t
39{
40 typedef Type item_t;
41 static constexpr unsigned item_size = hb_static_size (Type);
42 using array_t = typename std::conditional<sorted, hb_sorted_array_t<Type>, hb_array_t<Type>>::type;
43 using c_array_t = typename std::conditional<sorted, hb_sorted_array_t<const Type>, hb_array_t<const Type>>::type;
44
45 hb_vector_t () = default;
46 hb_vector_t (std::initializer_list<Type> lst) : hb_vector_t ()
47 {
48 alloc (size: lst.size (), exact: true);
49 for (auto&& item : lst)
50 push (item);
51 }
52 template <typename Iterable,
53 hb_requires (hb_is_iterable (Iterable))>
54 hb_vector_t (const Iterable &o) : hb_vector_t ()
55 {
56 auto iter = hb_iter (o);
57 if (iter.is_random_access_iterator)
58 alloc (size: hb_len (iter), exact: true);
59 hb_copy (iter, *this);
60 }
61 hb_vector_t (const hb_vector_t &o) : hb_vector_t ()
62 {
63 alloc (size: o.length, exact: true);
64 if (unlikely (in_error ())) return;
65 copy_vector (o);
66 }
67 hb_vector_t (hb_vector_t &&o)
68 {
69 allocated = o.allocated;
70 length = o.length;
71 arrayZ = o.arrayZ;
72 o.init ();
73 }
74 ~hb_vector_t () { fini (); }
75
76 public:
77 int allocated = 0; /* == -1 means allocation failed. */
78 unsigned int length = 0;
79 public:
80 Type *arrayZ = nullptr;
81
82 void init ()
83 {
84 allocated = length = 0;
85 arrayZ = nullptr;
86 }
87 void init0 ()
88 {
89 }
90
91 void fini ()
92 {
93 shrink_vector (size: 0);
94 hb_free (arrayZ);
95 init ();
96 }
97
98 void reset ()
99 {
100 if (unlikely (in_error ()))
101 /* Big Hack! We don't know the true allocated size before
102 * an allocation failure happened. But we know it was at
103 * least as big as length. Restore it to that and continue
104 * as if error did not happen. */
105 allocated = length;
106 resize (size_: 0);
107 }
108
109 friend void swap (hb_vector_t& a, hb_vector_t& b)
110 {
111 hb_swap (a.allocated, b.allocated);
112 hb_swap (a.length, b.length);
113 hb_swap (a.arrayZ, b.arrayZ);
114 }
115
116 hb_vector_t& operator = (const hb_vector_t &o)
117 {
118 reset ();
119 alloc (size: o.length, exact: true);
120 if (unlikely (in_error ())) return *this;
121
122 copy_vector (o);
123
124 return *this;
125 }
126 hb_vector_t& operator = (hb_vector_t &&o)
127 {
128 hb_swap (*this, o);
129 return *this;
130 }
131
132 hb_bytes_t as_bytes () const
133 { return hb_bytes_t ((const char *) arrayZ, get_size ()); }
134
135 bool operator == (const hb_vector_t &o) const { return as_array () == o.as_array (); }
136 bool operator != (const hb_vector_t &o) const { return !(*this == o); }
137 uint32_t hash () const { return as_array ().hash (); }
138
139 Type& operator [] (int i_)
140 {
141 unsigned int i = (unsigned int) i_;
142 if (unlikely (i >= length))
143 return Crap (Type);
144 return arrayZ[i];
145 }
146 const Type& operator [] (int i_) const
147 {
148 unsigned int i = (unsigned int) i_;
149 if (unlikely (i >= length))
150 return Null (Type);
151 return arrayZ[i];
152 }
153
154 Type& tail () { return (*this)[length - 1]; }
155 const Type& tail () const { return (*this)[length - 1]; }
156
157 explicit operator bool () const { return length; }
158 unsigned get_size () const { return length * item_size; }

160 /* Sink interface. */
161 template <typename T>
162 hb_vector_t& operator << (T&& v) { push (std::forward<T> (v)); return *this; }
163
164 array_t as_array () { return hb_array (arrayZ, length); }
165 c_array_t as_array () const { return hb_array (arrayZ, length); }

167 /* Iterator. */
168 typedef c_array_t iter_t;
169 typedef array_t writer_t;
170 iter_t iter () const { return as_array (); }
171 writer_t writer () { return as_array (); }
172 operator iter_t () const { return iter (); }
173 operator writer_t () { return writer (); }

175 /* Faster range-based for loop. */
176 Type *begin () const { return arrayZ; }
177 Type *end () const { return arrayZ + length; }

180 hb_sorted_array_t<Type> as_sorted_array ()
181 { return hb_sorted_array (arrayZ, length); }
182 hb_sorted_array_t<const Type> as_sorted_array () const
183 { return hb_sorted_array (arrayZ, length); }

185 template <typename T> explicit operator T * () { return arrayZ; }
186 template <typename T> explicit operator const T * () const { return arrayZ; }
187
188 Type * operator + (unsigned int i) { return arrayZ + i; }
189 const Type * operator + (unsigned int i) const { return arrayZ + i; }
190
191 Type *push ()
192 {
193 if (unlikely (!resize (length + 1)))
194 return &Crap (Type);
195 return std::addressof (arrayZ[length - 1]);
196 }
197 template <typename T,
198 typename T2 = Type,
199 hb_enable_if (!std::is_copy_constructible<T2>::value &&
200 std::is_copy_assignable<T>::value)>
201 Type *push (T&& v)
202 {
203 Type *p = push ();
204 if (p == &Crap (Type))
205 // If push failed to allocate then don't copy v, since this may cause
206 // the created copy to leak memory since we won't have stored a
207 // reference to it.
208 return p;
209 *p = std::forward<T> (v);
210 return p;
211 }
212 template <typename T,
213 typename T2 = Type,
214 hb_enable_if (std::is_copy_constructible<T2>::value)>
215 Type *push (T&& v)
216 {
217 if (unlikely (!alloc (length + 1)))
218 // If push failed to allocate then don't copy v, since this may cause
219 // the created copy to leak memory since we won't have stored a
220 // reference to it.
221 return &Crap (Type);
222
223 /* Emplace. */
224 length++;
225 Type *p = std::addressof (arrayZ[length - 1]);
226 return new (p) Type (std::forward<T> (v));
227 }
228
229 bool in_error () const { return allocated < 0; }
230
231 template <typename T = Type,
232 hb_enable_if (hb_is_trivially_copy_assignable(T))>
233 Type *
234 realloc_vector (unsigned new_allocated)
235 {
236 if (!new_allocated)
237 {
238 hb_free (arrayZ);
239 return nullptr;
240 }
241 return (Type *) hb_realloc (arrayZ, new_allocated * sizeof (Type));
242 }
243 template <typename T = Type,
244 hb_enable_if (!hb_is_trivially_copy_assignable(T))>
245 Type *
246 realloc_vector (unsigned new_allocated)
247 {
248 if (!new_allocated)
249 {
250 hb_free (arrayZ);
251 return nullptr;
252 }
253 Type *new_array = (Type *) hb_malloc (size: new_allocated * sizeof (Type));
254 if (likely (new_array))
255 {
256 for (unsigned i = 0; i < length; i++)
257 {
258 new (std::addressof (new_array[i])) Type ();
259 new_array[i] = std::move (arrayZ[i]);
260 arrayZ[i].~Type ();
261 }
262 hb_free (arrayZ);
263 }
264 return new_array;
265 }
266
267 template <typename T = Type,
268 hb_enable_if (hb_is_trivially_constructible(T))>
269 void
270 grow_vector (unsigned size)
271 {
272 memset (arrayZ + length, 0, (size - length) * sizeof (*arrayZ));
273 length = size;
274 }
275 template <typename T = Type,
276 hb_enable_if (!hb_is_trivially_constructible(T))>
277 void
278 grow_vector (unsigned size)
279 {
280 while (length < size)
281 {
282 length++;
283 new (std::addressof (arrayZ[length - 1])) Type ();
284 }
285 }
286
287 template <typename T = Type,
288 hb_enable_if (hb_is_trivially_copyable (T))>
289 void
290 copy_vector (const hb_vector_t &other)
291 {
292 length = other.length;
293#ifndef HB_OPTIMIZE_SIZE
294 if (sizeof (T) >= sizeof (long long))
295 /* This runs faster because of alignment. */
296 for (unsigned i = 0; i < length; i++)
297 arrayZ[i] = other.arrayZ[i];
298 else
299#endif
300 hb_memcpy (dst: (void *) arrayZ, src: (const void *) other.arrayZ, len: length * item_size);
301 }
302 template <typename T = Type,
303 hb_enable_if (!hb_is_trivially_copyable (T) &&
304 std::is_copy_constructible<T>::value)>
305 void
306 copy_vector (const hb_vector_t &other)
307 {
308 length = 0;
309 while (length < other.length)
310 {
311 length++;
312 new (std::addressof (arrayZ[length - 1])) Type (other.arrayZ[length - 1]);
313 }
314 }
315 template <typename T = Type,
316 hb_enable_if (!hb_is_trivially_copyable (T) &&
317 !std::is_copy_constructible<T>::value &&
318 std::is_default_constructible<T>::value &&
319 std::is_copy_assignable<T>::value)>
320 void
321 copy_vector (const hb_vector_t &other)
322 {
323 length = 0;
324 while (length < other.length)
325 {
326 length++;
327 new (std::addressof (arrayZ[length - 1])) Type ();
328 arrayZ[length - 1] = other.arrayZ[length - 1];
329 }
330 }
331
332 void
333 shrink_vector (unsigned size)
334 {
335 while ((unsigned) length > size)
336 {
337 arrayZ[(unsigned) length - 1].~Type ();
338 length--;
339 }
340 }
341
342 void
343 shift_down_vector (unsigned i)
344 {
345 for (; i < length; i++)
346 arrayZ[i - 1] = std::move (arrayZ[i]);
347 }
348
349 /* Allocate for size but don't adjust length. */
350 bool alloc (unsigned int size, bool exact=false)
351 {
352 if (unlikely (in_error ()))
353 return false;
354
355 unsigned int new_allocated;
356 if (exact)
357 {
358 /* If exact was specified, we allow shrinking the storage. */
359 size = hb_max (size, length);
360 if (size <= (unsigned) allocated &&
361 size >= (unsigned) allocated >> 2)
362 return true;
363
364 new_allocated = size;
365 }
366 else
367 {
368 if (likely (size <= (unsigned) allocated))
369 return true;
370
371 new_allocated = allocated;
372 while (size > new_allocated)
373 new_allocated += (new_allocated >> 1) + 8;
374 }
375
376
377 /* Reallocate */
378
379 bool overflows =
380 (int) in_error () ||
381 (new_allocated < size) ||
382 hb_unsigned_mul_overflows (count: new_allocated, size: sizeof (Type));
383
384 if (unlikely (overflows))
385 {
386 allocated = -1;
387 return false;
388 }
389
390 Type *new_array = realloc_vector (new_allocated);
391
392 if (unlikely (new_allocated && !new_array))
393 {
394 if (new_allocated <= (unsigned) allocated)
395 return true; // shrinking failed; it's okay; happens in our fuzzer
396
397 allocated = -1;
398 return false;
399 }
400
401 arrayZ = new_array;
402 allocated = new_allocated;
403
404 return true;
405 }
406
407 bool resize (int size_, bool initialize = true, bool exact = false)
408 {
409 unsigned int size = size_ < 0 ? 0u : (unsigned int) size_;
410 if (!alloc (size, exact))
411 return false;
412
413 if (size > length)
414 {
415 if (initialize)
416 grow_vector (size);
417 }
418 else if (size < length)
419 {
420 if (initialize)
421 shrink_vector (size);
422 }
423
424 length = size;
425 return true;
426 }
427 bool resize_exact (int size_, bool initialize = true)
428 {
429 return resize (size_, initialize, exact: true);
430 }
431
432 Type pop ()
433 {
434 if (!length) return Null (Type);
435 Type v {std::move (arrayZ[length - 1])};
436 arrayZ[length - 1].~Type ();
437 length--;
438 return v;
439 }
440
441 void remove_ordered (unsigned int i)
442 {
443 if (unlikely (i >= length))
444 return;
445 shift_down_vector (i: i + 1);
446 arrayZ[length - 1].~Type ();
447 length--;
448 }
449
450 template <bool Sorted = sorted,
451 hb_enable_if (!Sorted)>
452 void remove_unordered (unsigned int i)
453 {
454 if (unlikely (i >= length))
455 return;
456 if (i != length - 1)
457 arrayZ[i] = std::move (arrayZ[length - 1]);
458 arrayZ[length - 1].~Type ();
459 length--;
460 }
461
462 void shrink (int size_, bool shrink_memory = true)
463 {
464 unsigned int size = size_ < 0 ? 0u : (unsigned int) size_;
465 if (size >= length)
466 return;
467
468 shrink_vector (size);
469
470 if (shrink_memory)
471 alloc (size, exact: true); /* To force shrinking memory if needed. */
472 }

476 void qsort (int (*cmp)(const void*, const void*) = Type::cmp)

479 /* Unsorted search API. */

481 Type *lsearch (const T &x, Type *not_found = nullptr)

484 const Type *lsearch (const T &x, const Type *not_found = nullptr) const
485 { return as_array ().lsearch (x, not_found); }
486 template <typename T>
487 bool lfind (const T &x, unsigned *pos = nullptr) const
488 { return as_array ().lfind (x, pos); }
489
490 /* Sorted search API. */
491 template <typename T,
492 bool Sorted=sorted, hb_enable_if (Sorted)>
493 Type *bsearch (const T &x, Type *not_found = nullptr)
494 { return as_array ().bsearch (x, not_found); }
495 template <typename T,
496 bool Sorted=sorted, hb_enable_if (Sorted)>
497 const Type *bsearch (const T &x, const Type *not_found = nullptr) const
498 { return as_array ().bsearch (x, not_found); }
499 template <typename T,
500 bool Sorted=sorted, hb_enable_if (Sorted)>
501 bool bfind (const T &x, unsigned int *i = nullptr,
502 hb_not_found_t not_found = HB_NOT_FOUND_DONT_STORE,
503 unsigned int to_store = (unsigned int) -1) const
504 { return as_array ().bfind (x, i, not_found, to_store); }
505};
